'''Arnold Issoko''' (born 6 April 1992) is a [[Democratic Republic of the Congo|Congolese]] professional [[Association football|footballer]] who plays for French club [[Stade Malherbe Caen|Caen]] mainly as a [[Midfielder#Right Back|right back]] but also as a [[Midfielder#Right Winger|right winger]].<ref>{{cite web |title=ARNOLD ISAKO NOUVEL ATOUT DU STADE MALHERBE |url=https://www.smcaen.fr/2019-2020/actualites/groupe-pro/arnold-isako-nouvel-atout-du-stade-malherbe |publisher=SM Caen |accessdate=5 July 2019 |date=5 July 2019}}</ref>

Issoko made his debut for the [[DR Congo national football team]] in a friendly 1–1 tie with [[Romania national football team|Romania]] in May 2016.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.uefa.com/friendlies/season=2016/matches/round=2000582/match=2019899/postmatch/report/|title=Romania reined in by DR Congo|publisher=UEFA|first=Paul-Daniel|last=Zaharia|date=25 May 2016}}</ref>

